### Is this a regression?
Yes. It works as expected when `"enableIvy": false` is set in the `tsconfig.json` file. When ivy is enabled the behavior changes.

### Description
When using a custom directive on an `input` html element and binding `ngModel` the injected model in the directive is different once using ivy from when ivy is disabled. A side effect is that existing created directives no longer work when trying to update the model value using `this.modelInstance.update.emit`.


